<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-12C05EB7-B241-4D9D-B2F7-676AF8025DB2" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-12C05EB7-B241-4D9D-B2F7-676AF8025DB2" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">User Names &amp; Passwords</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M148543-B57"><p class="- topic/p ">This is an overview of the passwords used. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Preventive maintenance</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="M148543-B58" class="- topic/section "><title translate="no" class="- topic/title ">SDS</title><p class="- topic/p ">SDS does not require a password. You must insert the SAM key into the user interface to start SDS. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This SAM key needs to have the correct SDS license for this printing system. 
</p></section><section id="M148543-B60" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Printer operator panel / Settings editor</title><table id="M148543-TB61" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" outputclass="free" align="left" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="50*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" align="left" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" morerows="0" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">User 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" morerows="0" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Password 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" morerows="0" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">System administrator 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" morerows="0" valign="top" align="left" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 71617000 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p ">For security reason the customer should change the default "System administrator" password. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The system administrator can define his own password (Settings Editor: Configuration &gt; Users &gt; (System Administrator box checked) &gt; Edit). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">. 
</p><note id="GUID-C0342478-42F0-4F5D-9B59-F92F3E048F7A" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">In case this password is lost</b>, it can be reset by the system administrator himself (i.e., without Service intervention). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This procedure is performed by mean of an e-mail. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This requires configuring a mail server and a mail account in the Settings Editor (Configuration &gt; Mail server &gt; Edit) at installation time. 
</p></note><p class="- topic/p ">See the 
<xref keyref="ExtOperationGuide" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-250A5CF0-B4FF-4B2C-B7C2-66A319226098.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="reference"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Operation and Safety information?>Operation and Safety information</xref> for detailed information. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-53586EB2-B578-4240-83EB-4B8BC8331698" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Teamviewer</title><p class="- topic/p ">The Teamviewer password is : 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Teamviewer_495954</b> 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-AE482382-4925-4EFB-985E-8DF8BE795C1D.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Preventive maintenance</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
